xkcd color saliency map stanford vis group home papers people video stanford vis group color saliency from xkcd color terms each point represents a 5 5 5 bin in cie l a b color space slices for each l value are shown the area of each point is proportional to its saliency large points indicate consistently named colors small points indicate colors that exhibit high naming confusion the prominent clusters correspond to basic color terms identified by berlin & kay blue brown green grey pink purple etc note this page requires a modern browser capable of rendering svg rss stanford computer science
